external_knowledge:
- "prodigious fruits" metaphorically refers to the products;
- "garden of commerce" represents the database/warehouse where products are listed;
- "identities" and "origins" refer to the product ID and product name respectively;
- "seeds that bear them" symbolizes the category names as they define the type of products;
- "soil that nurtures them" signifies the sizes of the products, as sizes can be seen as the environment in which the product is measured;
- "pluck the first ten" corresponds to the LIMIT 10 clause in the SQL query, implying we only harvest/consider the first ten entries.

sql:
SELECT variant_id 
FROM product_variants 
WHERE stock_quantity > (SELECT AVG(stock_quantity) FROM product_variants);

external_knowledge:
- "treasures" refers to the products in the inventory;
- "hidden in the depths of the inventory" metaphorically describes products that are still available (stock quantity > 0);
- "identities" refers to the product IDs;
- "names" refers to the product names;
- "prices" refers to the cost of the products;
- "size that fits the English gentleman" refers to the UK men's size;
- "hue that adorns them" refers to the color names;
- "count how many have yet to find their owners" refers to the stock quantity.

sql:
SELECT products.product_name, materials.material_name 
FROM products 
JOIN materials ON products.material_id = materials.material_id;

SELECT products.product_id, users.user_name
FROM products
CROSS JOIN users;

external_knowledge:
- 'siblings' in this context refer to products that share the same category, brand, material, and color as 'product1';
- 'roots' metaphorically refer to the category, brand, material, and color that define a product's identity;
- 'family lineage' refers to the brand name and description, including the brand's website;
- 'elements that give them shape and hue' refer to the material and color information, including the material's properties and the color's hex code.

- 'main store' refers to store with ID 1;
- 'missing from the inventory' means the product does not appear in the store's inventory list (`si.product_id IS NULL`);
- 'average cost of items' corresponds to the average price of all products in the store, regardless of inventory status.

- "Typical amount" refers to the average quantity sold of all products;
- "Products" here refers to the items in the Products table;
- "Sold more than the typical amount" means the total quantity sold for a product is greater than the average total quantity sold for all products.
